HEADWORD: Similarity
<hw>Sim`i*lar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-ties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>similarit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
similar; likeness; resemblance; <as>as, a <ex>similarity</ex> of
features</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hardly is there a <qex>similarity</qex> detected between two or
three facts, than men hasten to extend it to all.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

